  have g := (Real.sqrt_lt_sqrt_iff (sq_nonneg ((q : ℝ) - 1))).mpr (h_ineq)
  have : Real.sqrt (((q:ℝ) - 1) ^ 2) = ((q : ℝ) - 1) := by sorry
  rw [this, Real.sqrt_sq] at g
  · exact g
  · sorry
```

Now we need to prove `⊢ 0 ≤ ‖eval (↑q) (X - C lamb)‖`.

We can use the fact that the norm of a complex number is always non-negative. In Lean, for any complex number `z : ℂ`, `‖z‖` is defined as `Real.sqrt (z.re ^ 2 + z.im ^ 2)`. Since `Real.sqrt` always returns a non-negative value, `‖z‖ ≥ 0`.

